@node "Intro" "Introduction"
@prev "contents"
@{b}Newsgroup Editor V3@{ub}

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

This is a program that was initially written to be part of the Control Panel
package, as I was given a lot of good feedback about this program I decided to
develop further.

The program basically edits your uulib:newsgroup file and allows you to keep a
list of inactive newsgroups which you can make active when you so wish by just
a few simple mouse clicks.

It also allows you to make brief notes on what the newsgroup is about, and
also allows unique signatures for each newsgroup (providing you are using Grn
and my postnews script which is included with this package).

This version also has several more advanced options such as the import file
utility, this utility allows you to add groups from a file such as your
suppliers active file just by specifying certain conditions. This enables you
to easily select all the newsgroups which are related to a certain subject,
i.e you can select all the groups with the word amiga in them.

The interface for this version has also been improved, the previous interface
was fine if you only had a few active and inactive groups, but could prove a
bit of a pain if you had many newsgroups. I hope that the improvements which I
have made are greeted positively by users of the current version.

Unfortunately this version of Newsed is not compatible with Control Panel 4,
all users of Control Panel 4 should upgrade to @{"version 5" link "" 0}, which is fully
compatible.
@endnode

@node "Using" "Using The Editor"
@prev "Intro"
@{b}Using the Editor@{ub}

On loading Newsed you will be faced with a screen which displays all the
current active and inactive newsgroups in a listviewgadget , as well as a few
buttons. The basic display looks something like this

                         Active Newsgroups
    -------------------------------------------------------
    |@{"demon.ip.support.amiga                             " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"zynet.local                                        " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"zynet.announce                                     " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"comp.sys.amiga.announce                            " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"uk.education.misc                                  " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    -------------------------------------------------------

                         Inactive Newsgroups
    -------------------------------------------------------
    |@{"alt.2600hz                                         " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"alt.2d                                             " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"alt.3d                                             " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"alt.3d.misc                                        " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    |@{"alt.3d.sirds                                       " link "Group Information" 0}| |
    -------------------------------------------------------

               @{"Add Group" link "addgroup" 0}  @{"Import" link "Import" 0}  @{"Save" link "save" 0}  @{"Cancel" link "cancel" 0}

By clicking on the above diagram you can find out more about how to use the
editor. Most of it should be pretty simple apart from the import facility
which is quite complex.
@endnode

@node "addgroup" "Add Group Gadget"
@toc "using"
@next "days"
@prev "cancel"
@{b}Adding A New Newsgroup@{ub}

Enter the name of the newsgroup you wish to add into the Group Name box, then
add the number of days you wish to keep articles posted to this newsgroup for.
If you wish the newsgroups to be added to your active group list, click on the
active box so that a tick appears.

@{fg highlight}@{"Edit Sig" link " " 0}@{fg text}

This button runs a text editor so that you can edit the signature file for
this group. To use this signature file you need to be using Grn and the
postnews replacement script which is inluded with this program.

@{fg highlight}@{"Edit info" link " " 0}@{fg text}

This allows you to write a brief description about the newsgroups, this
description can be displayed in the @{"group information" link "Group Information" 0} display.

@{fg highlight}@{"Add Group" link " " 0}@{fg text}

This actually adds the groups to the inactive or active files and add the
groups to the end of the relevant listview display on the main screen.

@{fg highlight}@{"Cancel" link " " 0}@{fg text}

Pressing this exits this part of the program, and changes nothing.
@endnode

@node "Import" "Import"
@toc "Using"
@{b}Import File@{ub}

This window allows you to import a complete file into the
uulib:newsgroup.inactive file, this is very handy for adding new newsgroup
files, or adding a new active file. It also allows you to just import groups
which match stated criteria, so you can add all the groups relating to one
subject.

@{fg highlight}@{"File To Import:" link "" 0} @{fg text}Name of file you wish to import into Newsed, you can either
                type this in the string gadget or press the F button to use
                a file requester.

@{fg highlight}@{"Days To Keep:" link "" 0} @{fg text}How many days do you want to keep the articles for these
              newsgroups, only necessary if adding to active file.

@{fg highlight}@{"Active:" link "" 0} @{fg text}A tick here indicates that you want to add the new groups to your
        active list, to change click on box.

@{fg highlight}@{"All:" link "" 0} @{fg text}Do you want to add all the groups in the file, if selected all the
     include and exclude options are disregarded.

Now for the advanced bit....

All the following string gadgets can contain more than one entry, to enter
more than one item please sepearate the items by a comma (,) e.g alt,comp,rec

@{fg highlight}@{"Include Hierarchy:" link "" 0}@{fg text} Hierarchies you wish to include, this basically matches
                   your entry with the left handside of the newsgroup name.

@{fg highlight}@{"Include Text:" link "" 0}@{fg text} Includes any newsgroup with this text anywhere in its name.

If both include gadgets are empty, all files will be selected unless you
exclude them with the exclude gadgets.

@{fg highlight}@{"Exclude Text:" link "" 0}@{fg text} Hierarchies you don't want to include, this basically matches
              your entry with the left handside of the newsgroup name.

@{fg highlight}@{"Exclude Text:" link "" 0}@{fg text} Excludes any newsgroup with this text anywhere in its name.

If both exclude gadgets are empty then all the files specified in the include
gadgets will be selected.

These basic operations then can be combined to provide a more complex group
selection, by selecting the and/or buttons next to the include or exclude
options.

Include

ICNo Include Hierarchy  Include Text  And/Or

1.   alt,demon          amiga         and      All groups in alt or demon
                                               hierarchies that contain the
                                               word amiga somewhere in their
name

2.   alt,demon          amiga         or       All groups that are in the alt
                                               and demon hierarchies as well
                                               as any groups that contain the
                                               word amiga.

The exclude options work in a similar way, but work on the groups selected by
the include options and not the whole file.

Mixed

The include and exclude options can be combined to create a very complex
selection, the include options are anded with the exclude options, i.e. the
exclude options are only applied to the groups selected by the include
options.

For example using ICno 1 from above and then specifying exclude text as misc,
would add all the groups in alt or demon that contain the word amiga but do
not include the word misc, so alt.amiga.1200 would be selected but
demon.amiga.1200.misc and comp.sys.amiga.misc would not.
@endnode

@node "Group Information" "Group Information                           "
@toc "Using"
@{b}Group Information@{ub}

This window shows you information about the group and allows you to change
several of the groups attributes.

@{fg highlight}@{"Group Name:" link ""}@{fg text} Displays the name of the selected group

@{fg highlight}@{"Days to Keep:" link ""}@{fg text} Shows the days the articles are to be kept,
              you may change this, by altering the number in the box.

@{fg highlight}@{"Active:" link ""}@{fg text} Whether the group is in the active list or not, a tick indicates
        that the group is active, you may change this by clicking in the
        box.

@{fg highlight}@{"Articles Received:" link ""}@{fg text} This is the number of articles which have been received
                   from that group, this can give an indication of how busy
                   that particular group is.

@{fg highlight}@{"Edit Description:" link ""}@{fg text} This allows you to edit a description about the newsgroup,
                  this is a useful memory jogger.
                  The gadget below displays the group description.

@{fg highlight}@{"Edit Signature:" link ""}@{fg text}   This allows you to edit the newsgroups signature,
                  only useful if you have Grn and my postnews script.
                  May modify script for tin, and include with registered
                  versions.
                  The gadget below displays the signature.

@{fg highlight}@{"Save Changes:" link ""}@{fg text} Saves any changes that you have made.

@{fg highlight}@{"Cancel:" link ""}@{fg text} Disregards any changes made.
@endnode

@node "save" "Save Gadget"
@toc "using"
@next "cancel"
@prev "more"
@{b}Save@{ub}

This gadget saves the changes made and then the programs exits after building
any new files.
@endnode

@node "cancel" "Cancel Gadget"
@toc "using"
@next "addgroup"
@prev "save"
@{b}Cancel@{ub}

This gadgets exits the program forgetting any changes made.
@endnode

